Revision history for Sub-Abstract

0.02
        [Bug fixes]
        - import(): fix eval/$@ clobber race -- a DESTROY fired between
          eval { validate_strict() } and if ($@) could silently swallow the
          validation error; use my $ok = eval { ...; 1 } pattern instead
        - import(): replace implicit $_ postfix-for iterators with explicit
          named for-my variables to avoid aliasing ambiguity
        - import(): remove duplicate set_return() call; single return path now

        [Enhancements]
        - Add carp alongside croak in Carp import for future non-fatal paths
        - _assert_private_caller(): simplify to single croak-unless guard
        - Improve all private-sub comment headers (Purpose/Entry/Exit/
          Side effects/Notes) for _wrap, _process_one, _assert_private_caller,
          UNIVERSAL::Abstract, and the CHECK block
        - Unused positional args in UNIVERSAL::Abstract handler bound to undef

        [Documentation]
        - import(): add =head3 PSEUDOCODE, API SPECIFICATION (input/output
          schemas), per-method FORMAL SPECIFICATION (Z notation), and a full
          MESSAGES table with causes and remediation steps
        - Add =head1 BUGS section documenting each fixed bug with the original
          code and the replacement
        - Expand =head1 KNOWN LIMITATIONS: bypass precedence ($BYPASS takes
          full priority over harness_bypass=0), thread safety, DESTROY on
          Perl 5.42+, _assert_private_caller as lint tool not security fence
        - Promote =head2 FORMAL SPECIFICATION to =head1; consolidate split
          POD blocks (remove spurious second =cut / re-opened block)
        - PUBLIC VARIABLES: document bypass precedence and truthy-string gotcha
        - Bypass section: document that both $BYPASS and harness_bypass must be
          cleared to test enforcement inside the harness

        [Tests]
        - t/locales.t: new file; verifies croak core message is bitwise-
          identical under en_US.UTF-8, de_DE.UTF-8, and zh_CN.UTF-8; documents
          use_ok incompatibility with CHECK-block modules; GeoIP dimension noted
          as not applicable

0.01	Wed Jun 10 12:02:36 EDT 2026
        First release
